Google launches a new AI ransomware detection feature for Drive on desktop, trained on millions of real victim files encrypted by various ransomware strains (Lily Hay Newman/Wired)
Amazon unveils the $220 Echo Studio, its high-end speaker for audiophiles, 8" and 11" Echo Show for $180 and $220, and the $100 Echo Dot Max, all with Alexa+ (Mark Gurman/Bloomberg)
Amazon launches new Fire TVs and a $40 Fire TV Stick 4K Select with a new OS called Vega and built in Alexa+ (Ryan Epps/Tom's Guide)
Vercel, which offers cloud tools to make web and AI apps, raised $300M led by Accel and Singapore's GIC at a $9.3B valuation and considers a ~$300M tender offer (Paayal Zaveri/Bloomberg)
Amazon updates the Kindle Scribe, including a $630 Kindle Scribe Colorsoft with a larger 11-inch E Ink display, lower weight at 400g, and a 5.4mm thin body (Andrew Liszewski/The Verge)
An interview with Ring founder Jamie Siminoff, who returned to the company in April, on why he "backs the blue", how Ring is fighting crime, Amazon, and more (Annie Palmer/CNBC)
Amazon's Ring unveils the $200 Outdoor Cam Pro, $250 Spotlight Cam Pro, $280 Floodlight Cam Pro with Retinal Vision, a Search Party tool to find pets, and more (Mark Gurman/Bloomberg)
Apple-owned Beats announces the $200 Powerbeats Fit, with a redesigned wingtip, IPX4 rating for the case, ANC, and Apple's H1 chip, available October 2 (Chris Welch/Bloomberg)
A live blog of Amazon's fall 2025 hardware event in New York City (The Verge)
Google updates AI Mode to make searching through images using vague descriptions easier and says the tool will "provide a relevant set of shoppable options" (Jess Weatherbed/The Verge)
Anthropic now requires users to accept new privacy terms by October 8, including choosing whether new chats and coding sessions can be used to train AI models (Reece Rogers/Wired)
Microsoft launches a Security Store with SaaS tools and AI agents from Darktrace and others, and now lets Security Copilot users build their own AI agents (Tom Warren/The Verge)
DoorDash unveils delivery robot Dot, standing 4-foot, 6-inches tall and able to carry up to 30lb of cargo at up to 20mph, and a smart scale for restaurants (Natalie Lung/Bloomberg)
Adobe launches its Premiere video editing software on iPhone for the first time; general editing is free, but Adobe charges for credits to generate AI content (Chris Welch/Bloomberg)
Chipmaker Cerebras Systems raised a $1.1B Series G from Fidelity, Trump Jr.'s 1789 Capital, and others at an $8.1B post-money valuation ahead of its planned IPO (Rebecca Szkutak/TechCrunch)
